  "text": "The Apache Kafka audit logging for authorization decisions is implemented through the following components:\n\n1. **Authorization Result Types**: In `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/authorizer/AuthorizationResult.java`, the enum defines ALLOWED and DENIED authorization results that are the basis for audit logging.\n\n2. **Action Configuration**: In `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/authorizer/Action.java`, the Action class contains critical fields `logIfAllowed()` and `logIfDenied()` that control whether authorization decisions should be logged. These flags determine if access grants or denials should be recorded in the audit trail for ACL decisions.\n\n3. **Authorization Helper**: In `core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/AuthHelper.scala`, the AuthHelper class coordinates authorization checks by creating Action objects with appropriate logIfAllowed and logIfDenied flags (lines 52, 67, 111) and delegating to the Authorizer plugin for actual authorization and audit logging.\n\n4. **Audit Logging Implementation**: The primary audit logging for authorization decisions occurs in `metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/StandardAuthorizerData.java`. This class contains:\n   - An `auditLog` logger instance (lines 82, 115-116)\n   - `logAuditMessage()` method (lines 281-310) that logs ALLOWED events at debug level and DENIED events at info level when logIfAllowed/logIfDenied flags are set\n   - `buildAuditMessage()` method (lines 254-271) that constructs detailed audit messages including principal, operation, resource, host, and authorization result\n\n5. **Authorizer Interface**: In `metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/StandardAuthorizer.java`, the StandardAuthorizer class implements the Authorizer interface and delegates authorization decisions to StandardAuthorizerData, which produces the audit log entries for authorization decisions using the audit trail functionality."
}

